<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: lack of melee on pvp server</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Stupid">Stupid</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:39 p.m. 27/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: lack of melee on pvp server<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1933" TARGET=_self>lack of meele on pvp server</A> (blarg)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I have noticed that most ppl who play on pvp server are mostly

<BR>&gt; spellcasters. Now its true that mages dish out some sinister
<BR>&gt; dmg, but wouldnt a paldin rock anyone solo (and be a great group
<BR>&gt; addition)at higher lvl
<P>I play a Paladin on the side. My primary character is a Troll Shaman, but when I get tired of sitting and meditating all the time I switch to the Paladin. And you know what? You're absolutely right. Paladins do rock, but you really have to be a lot more careful with them. The "lay hands" thing is only good once each day (about every 90 minutes realtime) so it is not to be used lightly. I think I've used it twice so far, total. Each time it was a life-or-death situation. And it surprised the hell out of at least one silly Dark Elf Necromancer that took me for an easy kill!!
<P>I will say this: playing a Paladin requires a lot more "finesse" than a spellcaster. Until you reach level nine, you're so much cannon fodder. In contrast, a Necromancer (which seems to be a REALLY popular class) is a virtual killing machine by the time they reach level four. Of course, by the time they reach ten or so, THEY are cannon fodder, so it all evens out.
<P>God help me if/when I get a Holy Sword. I'll be hooked for life.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
